{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782539303679,"sessionID":"ses_0f863e659ffe0XQS54yysW5yx4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_MpDBATROVI1smnX4tBO2lU8i","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: temp-platform-capability-phase02-patch.json\n+{\n+  \"schemaVersion\": 1,\n+  \"purpose\": \"Resolve phase-02 startup/session/navigation platform capabilities with source-confirmed applicability and HarmonyOS Cangjie evidence.\",\n+  \"updates\": [\n+    {\n+      \"capabilityId\": \"runtime-permissions\",\n+      \"set\": {\n+        \"status\": \"not-applicable\",\n+        \"targetCapabilitySearch\": [\n+          \"Phase-02 source inspection found no Android runtime permission request or protected-API flow in the startup/session/navigation implementation scope: `presentation/MainActivity.kt`, `presentation/common/SplashViewModel.kt`, `data/repository/LoginRepositoryImpl.kt`, `FoodikeApp.kt`, and `di/AppModule.kt` contain splash gating, DataStore session persistence, `Application`, and DI wiring but no `requestPermissions`, `Manifest.permission`, Activity Result permission launcher, or permission-result handling.\",\n+          \"Repository-wide source grep over `D:\\\\Kotlin2Cangjie\\\\Foodike\\\\app\\\\src\\\\main\\\\java` found DataStore and `Application` usage only for this phase surface; it did not find `requestPermissions`, `rememberLauncherForActivityResult`, `ActivityResultContracts.RequestPermission`, `READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE`, `WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE`, `POST_NOTIFICATIONS`, `Service`, `BroadcastReceiver`, `WorkManager`, or notification APIs in the inspected phase sources.\",\n+          \"Current Cangjie SDK does provide a callable runtime-permission path through `AtManager.requestPermissionsFromUser(context: UIAbilityContext, permissionList: Array<Permissions>, requestCallback: AsyncCallback<PermissionRequestResult>)` and `PermissionRequestResult`, so this row is closed as phase-specific not-applicable