mUserUIAbilityC_82361e31.md`).\",\n+          \"HarmonyOS security guide documents the runtime authorization flow for Cangjie apps (`D:\\\\workspace\\\\Foodike\\\\.agents\\\\skills\\\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\\\Guide\\\\security\\\\AccessToken\\\\cj-request-user-authorization\\\\向用户申请授权\\\\开发步骤\\\\开发步骤_1.md`).\"\n+        ],\n+        \"discoveryOnlyEvidence\": [],\n+        \"compileProbeEvidence\": [],\n+        \"preResolutionDecision\": \"resolved-not-applicable\",\n+        \"phaseCapabilityResolution\": \"resolved-not-applicable\",\n+        \"blocker\": \"\",\n+        \"targetFallback\": \"\",\n+        \"futureCompletionPath\": \"\",\n+        \"notes\": \"Phase 02 only needs persisted session state, splash/start-destination gating, and in-app navigation shell behavior. The installed SDK supports runtime permission prompts, but the current phase source evidence does not require any protected platform access. Keep permission handling for later capability rows such as media/file access if those source-backed features are implemented.\",\n+        \"capabilityFacts\": {\n+          \"schemaVersion\": 1,\n+          \"resolutionKind\": \"not-applicable\",\n+          \"activeFallback\": {\n+            \"used\": false,\n+            \"fallbackKind\": \"\",\n+            \"reason\": \"\",\n+            \"blocker\": \"\"\n+          },\n+          \"apiEvidence\": [\n+            {\n+              \"kind\": \"cangjie-sdk-declaration\",\n+              \"detail\": \"`AtManager.requestPermissionsFromUser(...)` exists in `ohos.ability_access_ctrl.cj.d:163-164`, proving the platform capability exists in current Cangjie SDK even though this phase does not need it.\"\n+            },\n+            {\n+              \"kind\": \"cangjie-callable-api\",\n+              \"detail\": \"AbilityKit Cangjie docs document `requestPermissionsFromUser` as the direct runtime authorization API.\"\n+            }\n+          ],\n+          \"discoveryOnlyEvidence\": [],\n+          \"compileProbeEvidence\": [],\n+          \"targetEndpoints\": [],\n+          \"blocker\": {\n+            \"used\": false,\n+            \"kind\": \"\",\n+            \"detail\": \"\",\n+            \"futureCompletionPath\": \"\"\n+          },\n+          \"factsSource\": \"agent\"\n+        }\n+      }\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"capabilityId\": \"background-and-platform-components\",\n+      \"set\": {\n+        \"status\": \"platform-replaced\",\n+        \"targetCapabilitySearch\": [\n+          \"Phase-02 source inspection confirmed real app-entry and lifecycle scope, but not Android background services/receivers/widgets: `FoodikeApp.kt` defines `class FoodikeApp : Application()`, `MainActivity.kt` defines a single `ComponentActivity` with `installSplashScreen().setKeepOnScreenCondition { splashViewModel.isLoading.value }`, and `SplashViewModel.kt` resolves onboarding vs home from persisted login state before normal UI rendering.\",\n+          \"Current Cangjie SDK declares HarmonyOS app-entry and lifecycle APIs through `UIAbility`, `UIAbilityContext`, and ability startup methods such as `startAbility` / `startAbilityForResult`, which are the direct target replacement for the source `Application` + `Activity` startup surface.\",\n+          \"HarmonyOS Cangjie navigation docs recommend ArkUI `Navigation`/`NavPathStack` or `Router` for in-app page routing, so the source single-activity navigation shell should be implemented as HarmonyOS app bootstrap plus ArkUI navigation rather than Android activity/navigation infrastructure.\"\n+        ],\n+        \"targetApiOrLibrary\": \"HarmonyOS Cangjie AbilityKit app-entry APIs (`ohos.app.ability.ui_ability.UIAbility`, `UIAbilityContext`, `Want`) plus ArkUI `Navigation`/`NavPathStack` or `Router` for in-app startup and route flow\",\n+        \"targetStrategy\": \"Resolve the source Android platform component surface as a HarmonyOS platform replacement: model app startup in the target `UIAbility`/descriptor entry, keep splash-like gating inside bootstrap state before rendering the main route, and implement onboarding/home navigation using the existing ArkUI route shell instead of Android `Application`, `ComponentActivity`, and `core-splashscreen` APIs.\",\n+        \"targetEndpoints\": [\n+          \"AppScope/app.json5\",\n+          \"entry/src/main/module.json5\",\n+          \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj\",\n+          \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/app_router.cj\"\n+        ],\n+        \"tests\": [\n+          \"phase-02 startup-session-tests\",\n+          \"build_hap_report.py --phase phase-02-startup-session-navigation\"\n+        ],\n+        \"sdkDeclarationEvidence\": [\n+          \"Cangjie SDK declares `public open class UIAbility <: Ability` in `C:\\\\Users\\\\Sieger\\\\.cangjie-sdk\\\\6.0\\\\cangjie\\\\api\\\\modules\\\\linux_ohos_aarch64_cjnative\\\\ohos\\\\ohos.app.ability.ui_ability.cj.d:228`.\",\n+          \"Cangjie SDK declares `public open func onCreate(want: Want, launchParam: LaunchParam): Unit` for `UIAbility` in `C:\\\\Users\\\\Sieger\\\\.cangjie-sdk\\\\6.0\\\\cangjie\\\\api\\\\modules\\\\linux_ohos_aarch64_cjnative\\\\ohos\\\\ohos.app.ability.ui_ability.cj.d:276`.\",\n+          \"Cangjie SDK declares `public open class UIAbilityContext <: Context` plus `startAbility` / `startAbilityForResult` in `C:\\\\Users\\\\Sieger\\\\.cangjie-sdk\\\\6.0\\\\cangjie\\\\api\\\\modules\\\\linux_ohos_aarch64_cjnative\\\\ohos\\\\ohos.app.ability.ui_ability.cj.d:366,416,507,552`.\"\n+        ],\n+        \"cangjieCallableEvidence\": [\n+          \"HarmonyOS Cangjie docs describe `UIAbilityContext` as the lifecycle and ability-interaction context, including `startAbility` and `startAbilityForResult` (`D:\\\\workspace\\\\Foodike\\\\.agents\\\\skills\\\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\\\API\\\\AbilityKit\\\\cj-apis-app-ability-ui_ability\\\\ohosappabilityui_ability\\\\class_UIAbilityContext\\\\.overview.md`).\",\n+          \"HarmonyOS Cangjie docs describe ArkUI `Navigation` as the route-navigation root view container and recommend component navigation for page routing (`D:\\\\workspace\\\\Foodike\\\\.agents\\\\skills\\\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\\\API\\\\arkui-cj\\\\cj-navigation-switching-navigation\\\\Navigation\\\\.overview.md`; `D:\\\\workspace\\\\Foodike\\\\.agents\\\\skills\\\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\\\Guide\\\\arkui-cj\\\\cj-navigation-introduction\\\\cj-navigation-introduction.md`).\",\n+          \"HarmonyOS Cangjie docs also expose `Router` for page jumps when a lighter route shell is preferred (`D:\\\\workspace\\\\Foodike\\\\.agents\\\\skills\\\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\\\API\\\\arkui-cj\\\\cj-apis-uicontext-router\\\\Router\\\\class_Router.md`).\"\n+        ],\n+        \"discoveryOnlyEvidence\": [],\n+        \"compileProbeEvidence\": [],\n+        \"preResolutionDecision\": \"resolved-platform-replacement\",\n+        \"phaseCapabilityResolution\": \"resolved-platform-replacement\",\n+        \"blocker\": \"\",\n+        \"targetFallback\": \"\",\n+        \"futureCompletionPath\": \"\",\n+        \"notes\": \"This row is resolved for phase 02 as a real target architecture decision, not as a deferred background-services feature. The source phase only needs app entry, startup lifecycle gating, and route bootstrap; it does not require Android-equivalent services, receivers, widgets, or notifications. Phase implementation may proceed using HarmonyOS `UIAbility` plus the existing ArkUI route shell.\",\n+        \"capabilityFacts\": {\n+          \"schemaVersion\": 1,\n+          \"resolutionKind\": \"platform-replacement\",\n+          \"activeFallback\": {\n+            \"used\": false,\n+            \"fallbackKind\": \"\",\n+            \"reason\": \"\",\n+            \"blocker\": \"\"\n+          },\n+          \"apiEvidence\": [\n+          